webwork.pg-code:
Context()->flags->set( reduceConstants => 0, reduceConstantFunctions => 0,   );
Context()->variables->add(y=>"Real");
$P = Formula("8x+10y");
$A = Point(0,400);
$B = Point(400,200);
$C = Point(500,0);
$answer= Formula("$A,$B,$C");
$my_evaluator = $answer -> cmp(
 showHints=>1,
 showLengthHints => 1,
 partialCredit => 1,
); 
$P1 = $P->eval(x=>0, y=>400);
$P2 = $P->eval(x=>400, y=>200);
$P3 = $P->eval(x=>500, y=>0);

Context("Point");
$a = Point(400,200);
@choices = ("?","DNE","None", "Undefined");
$popup = PopUp([@choices], $choices[0]);  # It doesn't matter which is used as the "correct answer".
Context($popup->context); 
$b = OneOf(@choices[1..3]);

li.p:
{\text{Number of packages purchased from Company A: }~~x} 
                {\text{Number of packages purchased from Company B: } ~~y}
        First, we write the objective function. The store would like to minimize its cost, so
                C = 15x + 25y
        Next, we write the constraints. These will be a system of inequalities. It may help to organize the information into a table.

image.latex-image:

\tikzset{%
}
